name: 2,3,4,5-Tetrafluoro-N-(4-fluorophenyl)-6-hydroxybenzamide

The amide group typically increases the melting point significantly due its ability to form strong hydrogen bonds; this could be estimated to contribute around 80°C. The hydroxy group also forms hydrogen bonds, which could be estimated to raise the melting point by 40°C. The overall summation might need to be adjusted because of potential cooperative or diminishing effects among the functional groups when they are co-present in a compound.
